Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.54,0:02:29.35,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The old man's college buddies had a reunion at the hot spring resort, Benkei.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.35,0:02:32.31,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The attendees were the club manager, Yumi Horikoshi,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.31,0:02:35.94,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}the model shop owner, Jun Omura,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.94,0:02:38.68,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}the high school gym instructor, Yukio Ayashiro,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.68,0:02:41.26,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}his wife, Noriko Ayashiro,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.26,0:02:44.28,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}the Chiba Prefectural Police detective, Kazushi Nakamichi,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.28,0:02:47.40,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and then me, Ran, and the old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.40,0:02:51.01,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}We went to wake up Yumi Horikoshi,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.01,0:02:53.18,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}who was still in her room after the fireworks show ended,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.18,0:02:54.99,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}only to find that she had committed suicide
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.99,0:02:56.76,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}by shooting herself in the head!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.32,0:03:02.65,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}A makeshift autopsy showed that she had died seven hours earlier—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.65,0:03:06.05,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}at around 3:00 PM, when everyone was playing ping-pong
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.05,0:03:07.71,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}before leaving for the fireworks show!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.98,0:02:32.36,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}{\fad(500,0)}Cosmetic Company Employee\NYumi Horikoshi (37)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.90,0:02:35.40,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Model Shop Owner\NJun Omura (37)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.57,0:02:38.36,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,High School Gym Teacher\NYukio Ayashiro (38)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.82,0:02:40.91,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Housewife\NNoriko Ayashiro (37)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.41,0:02:43.91,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Chiba Prefectural Police Detective\NKazushi Nakamichi (38)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.20,0:03:18.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! Mouri! What is it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.59,0:03:20.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mouri!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.74,0:03:21.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me, Nakamichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.98,0:03:23.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Normally when someone commits suicide with a gun,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.99,0:03:26.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,they stick the barrel against their head, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.72,0:03:27.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.31,0:03:30.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then her bullet wound is missing something vital.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.93,0:03:36.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You're right! Burn marks!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.70,0:03:38.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.39,0:03:39.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When you shoot a gun,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.67,0:03:42.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,a stream of hot air accompanies the bullet!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.32,0:03:45.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you shoot with the gun against your head,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.68,0:03:48.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,it would have to leave burn marks behind!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.22,0:03:50.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The fact that there are none here means...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.45,0:03:54.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...t-that someone else shot her?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.22,0:03:55.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.27,0:03:58.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone shot her and then tried to make it look like a suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.95,0:04:01.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone in this inn...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.37,0:04:15.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't think one of us did it, do you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.80,0:04:17.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now. Don't get ahead of yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.95,0:04:21.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I just said the murder took place at approximately 3:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.70,0:04:24.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That was right after she went off on her own.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.11,0:04:27.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We were all in the ping-pong\Nroom from 3:00 to 6:00,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.80,0:04:29.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so none of us could have done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.89,0:04:32.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The only time someone left
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.40,0:04:34.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,was when Omura went to the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.72,0:04:37.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But that was well past 5:00,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.10,0:04:39.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and he came back in less than a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.44,0:04:41.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So then it was an outside job?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.40,0:04:43.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, perhaps.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.90,0:04:49.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As you can see,{I think this may be wrong -uso.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.41,0:04:51.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the killer could have gone anywhere along the roof,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.52,0:04:54.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,plus the door wasn't locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.60,0:04:57.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's very conceivable that someone entered from outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.86,0:05:01.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,At any rate, let's hear what the employees have to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.85,0:05:05.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone might've seen a suspicious character.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.75,0:05:11.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Anybody suspicious?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.18,0:05:15.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We were all out to lunch at three o'clock,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.86,0:05:20.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and even after we came back, there was no one that suspicious—
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.39,0:05:22.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Actually, there was such a person!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.10,0:05:25.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What were they like?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.19,0:05:27.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A young lass with a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.41,0:05:32.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She seemed very distraught and rushed straight upstairs!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.10,0:05:34.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you describe this girl?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.20,0:05:36.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, she's right there behind you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.13,0:05:38.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was those two young'uns.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.34,0:05:45.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe that was around 6:30,\Njust when the fireworks started...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.31,0:05:47.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She's talking about when we came to wake Yumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} up
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.60,0:05:50.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so she wouldn't miss the fireworks!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.10,0:05:51.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.66,0:05:55.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We went to her room and were about to go in, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.82,0:05:57.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I stopped them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.68,0:05:59.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She gets grumpy when people wake her up,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.51,0:06:01.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so I figured it best that they didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.65,0:06:05.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nakamichi? You were still here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.95,0:06:08.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I had worked up a sweat playing ping-pong
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.76,0:06:11.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so I took a quick dip in the public bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.37,0:06:16.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I felt bad for making you and Omura\Ngo on ahead and save our spot,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.60,0:06:19.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but you two were taking a bath too, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.91,0:06:23.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. We were in the open-air bath, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.28,0:06:28.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If only we had gone to wake\Nher up, she might still be—
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.35,0:06:31.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.06,0:06:34.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yumi died while we were playin' ping-pong!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.55,0:06:36.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We would've been too late no matter what...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.15,0:06:39.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say. Can I ask you something?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.08,0:06:41.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, Omura.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.10,0:06:43.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're hiding something, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.77,0:06:46.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You've been acting strange since this evening!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.20,0:06:49.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come clean! What're you hiding?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.92,0:06:51.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.92,0:06:53.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me you did this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.28,0:06:55.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw her!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.06,0:06:56.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When I left to go to the bathroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.66,0:06:59.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You saw the killer?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.21,0:07:01.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No! I saw Yumi!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.89,0:07:03.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What are you talking about?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.73,0:07:06.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was after 5:00 when you went to the bathroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.35,0:07:08.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yumi was already dead by then!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.83,0:07:10.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-That's just it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.47,0:07:13.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw her even though she was dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.23,0:07:16.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She was glaring at the ping-pong\Nroom from an upstairs window!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.97,0:07:19.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That can't be! Yumi was already dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.95,0:07:22.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be stupid! That's impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.55,0:07:27.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What if what I actually saw was her... her...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.33,0:07:33.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Get serious! There's no such thing as ghosts!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.94,0:07:37.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your mind was just confused because you were tired!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.91,0:07:39.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You were just imagining things!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.91,0:07:41.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah, maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.45,0:07:44.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Er...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.56,0:07:47.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did something happen at our inn?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.55,0:07:49.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's all this about ghosts and dying?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.36,0:07:52.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My friend was shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.75,0:07:56.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then they need medical treatment right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.36,0:07:58.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's too late for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.23,0:08:00.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The police are on their way as we speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.63,0:08:04.25,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Wait a minute! That's strange!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.25,0:08:06.54,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Why did that person say that at that time?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.38,0:08:12.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me the murderer is one of you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.65,0:08:14.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.38,0:08:17.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The murderer was someone else! Don't worry!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.65,0:08:18.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! Where are you—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.80,0:08:21.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nakamichi! You're in charge!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.01,0:08:22.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I gotta use the bathroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.05,0:08:24.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Mouri!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.73,0:08:31.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, isn't it too early to tell\Nthat this was an outside job?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.02,0:08:32.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, the way Yumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was killed was—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.81,0:08:38.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Quiet! I don't need any of your babbling!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.57,0:08:41.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This was no outside job!{uso: Outside job, my ass!}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.53,0:08:44.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Would someone who snuck in from outside
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.03,0:08:46.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,kill somebody and make it look like a suicide?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.79,0:08:48.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This was an inside job!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.73,0:08:51.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, it was one of my best friends!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.38,0:08:56.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know why or how they did it,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.24,0:08:59.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but I won't let them get away with this!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.62,0:09:02.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll expose them for what they are! This I swear!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.77,0:09:07.03,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Old man...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.22,0:09:12.11,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.11,0:09:14.67,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}One of those four is the murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.67,0:09:17.89,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}No, I have a good idea who it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.89,0:09:21.53,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It's most likely the person\Nwho said that one odd thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.53,0:09:23.87,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But that person has a perfect alibi—
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.89,0:09:25.33,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}{\a6}Ping-Pong Room
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.87,0:09:27.46,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}they were in the ping-pong room with everyone else!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.16,0:09:30.97,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I checked Yumi{\rHonorifics - Thoughts}-san{\r}'s estimated time of death for myself,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.97,0:09:32.20,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}so that can't be wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.74,0:09:35.48,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}In which case, how did that person kill her?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.58,0:09:37.79,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What bothers me
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.79,0:09:40.20,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}is the fact that Yumi{\rHonorifics - Thoughts}-san{\r}'s\Nfinger wasn't on the trigger
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.20,0:09:42.11,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}of the gun placed in her hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.71,0:09:44.28,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}You would expect the killer to put her finger on it
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.28,0:09:46.21,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}to fake her suicide...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.21,0:09:49.40,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It also bothers me that she didn't\Nhave any undergarments on
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.40,0:09:51.74,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and that she had{\rHonorifics - Thoughts} chan{\r}ged into a large yukata...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.26,0:09:56.11,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Did the killer{\rHonorifics - Thoughts} chan{\r}ge her clothes?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.11,0:09:57.13,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What for?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.83,0:10:08.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Benkei...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.20,0:10:13.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, that's\Nthe name of this inn, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.62,0:10:15.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The fact all these arrows are stuck in him
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.90,0:10:17.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,must mean this is from when\NBenkei died standing up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.29,0:10:22.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Died standing up?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.00,0:10:29.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it! Benkei!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.28,0:10:30.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer used this!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.70,0:10:34.14,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I've finally figured out the trick the killer used!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.94,0:10:44.35,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Here goes!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.35,0:10:48.01,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I'll just put the old man to sleep like always\Nwith my Tranquilizer Watch Gun...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.75,0:11:02.74,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}This was an inside job!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.74,0:11:06.14,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}In other words, it was one of my best friends!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.14,0:11:09.94,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I won't let them get away with this!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.94,0:11:13.28,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I'll expose them for what they are! This I swear!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.85,0:11:20.01,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Understood, old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.39,0:11:24.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But why did the killer shoot her?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.04,0:11:25.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps the killer came to steal her things
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.81,0:11:27.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but shot her when she spotted him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.87,0:11:30.30,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.30,0:11:35.50,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The killer has to be in here,\Nso why do they all have alibis?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.50,0:11:37.71,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Judging from the state of her rigor mortis,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.71,0:11:40.75,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Yumi's estimated time of\Ndeath was around 3:00 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.75,0:11:43.96,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Which means she was murdered\Nimmediately after she left us
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.96,0:11:46.81,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and returned to her room.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.81,0:11:50.80,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The rest of us were in the\Nping-pong room from 3:00 to 6:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.80,0:11:52.80,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Nobody had the{\rHonorifics - Thoughts} chan{\r}ce to kill her.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.80,0:11:55.82,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What bothers me is what Omura said...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.51,0:11:58.29,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}T-That's just it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.29,0:12:00.86,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I saw her even though she was dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.86,0:12:05.03,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}She was glaring at the ping-pong\Nroom from an upstairs window!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.03,0:12:07.88,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Omura went to the bathroom just after 5:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.88,0:12:09.60,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Yumi couldn't have been alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.14,0:12:12.58,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}So why did Omura say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.04,0:12:14.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Uncle...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.20,0:12:18.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's play ping-pong! Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.10,0:12:19.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.73,0:12:22.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}! What are you\Nsaying at a time like this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.60,0:12:24.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't play?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.27,0:12:26.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My shakehand grip is pretty good, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.77,0:12:29.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That reminds me, Yumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} used\Nthe shakehand grip too, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.98,0:12:33.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Remember? You saw it too,\Ndidn't you, Ran-{\i1}neechan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.25,0:12:36.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She was holding a racket with\Na shakehand-style in that picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.36,0:12:39.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.33,0:12:42.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But you can't play right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.52,0:12:43.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.18,0:12:44.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.45,0:12:46.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd have to{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ge clothes if I got all sweaty.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.31,0:12:50.58,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Sweat? Change clothes?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.58,0:12:52.58,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Shakehand grip?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.58,0:12:57.40,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Come to think of it, Yumi had\Nchanged into a large yukata...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.40,0:12:59.08,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and had nothing on underneath!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.08,0:13:02.84,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And her right index finger stuck out stiffly
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.84,0:13:06.01,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}instead of being on the trigger!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.01,0:13:07.40,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}With the shakehand grip,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.40,0:13:10.29,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}you hold the racket with your index finger out.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.29,0:13:13.34,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Could Yumi have been playing\Nping-pong with the murderer
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.34,0:13:15.45,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}before she was killed?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.45,0:13:19.52,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That's ridiculous. What purpose would that serve?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.52,0:13:20.83,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.83,0:13:24.09,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I could swear they mentioned\Nsomething at the police academy—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.85,0:13:30.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, didn't Benkei die while standing up?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.35,0:13:32.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.02,0:13:35.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Benkei fought hordes of enemies off\Nall by himself
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.43,0:13:38.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and then died on his feet when\Nthey showered him with arrows!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.86,0:13:41.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Oh! That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.01,0:13:46.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Mouri. What's the shouting about?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.14,0:13:52.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I've finally figured out who killed Yumi!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.42,0:13:53.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.70,0:13:55.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is it, Dad?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.76,0:13:58.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You were the one who killed Yumi!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.66,0:14:08.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You were the one who killed Yumi!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.68,0:14:11.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Nakamichi killed her?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.76,0:14:14.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, stop joking around...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.13,0:14:18.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was in the ping-pong room with everyone else\Nat her estimated time of death!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.96,0:14:21.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, your alibi is perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.66,0:14:25.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Assuming she really was killed at 3:00 PM!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.33,0:14:30.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?\NWe checked her time of death together!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.85,0:14:35.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yumi's toes were indeed beginning to stiffen,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.66,0:14:40.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so I estimated that she had\Ndied over seven hours prior.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.40,0:14:41.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But there are exceptions:
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.80,0:14:45.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,sudden deaths during intense physical exertion.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.71,0:14:50.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In such situations, intramuscular\Nproteins harden more easily,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.93,0:14:54.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,causing rigor mortis to take\Neffect much more quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.69,0:14:59.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Just like the heroic Musashibo Benkei!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.27,0:15:03.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So Benkei's death while standing up—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.65,0:15:07.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. It's been medically proven
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.05,0:15:09.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that it's possible to die while standing up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.05,0:15:12.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, now. The body was in Yumi's own room!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.94,0:15:16.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of exercise are\Nyou saying I made her do?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.75,0:15:21.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, she wasn't forced to\Nexert herself in her room—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.15,0:15:22.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,it was in the ping-pong room!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.58,0:15:26.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You made her play ping-pong\Nright up until you killed her!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.99,0:15:32.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You were most likely supposed to meet her all alone in the ping-pong room.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.24,0:15:36.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But then you invited us all into the room!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.70,0:15:39.61,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Oh yeah! What do you say\Nwe play some ping-pong now?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.61,0:15:41.43,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Sounds great!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.43,0:15:42.73,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I'll pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.73,0:15:46.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, Yumi grew angry\Nand returned to her room.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.53,0:15:49.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After 6:00, when everyone had left,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.45,0:15:53.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yumi went by herself to the ping-pong room, where you were waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.09,0:15:55.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It must've been quite the secret rendezvous.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.88,0:15:59.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You then invited her to a game of ping-pong.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.75,0:16:02.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After making her exert herself for a while,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.07,0:16:04.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you got her to return to her room...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.97,0:16:16.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...at which point you shot her in the head.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.64,0:16:22.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,All to skew the estimated time of\Ndeath and create the perfect alibi!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.33,0:16:25.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You likely used Yumi's short\Ntemper to your advantage
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.41,0:16:29.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to get her to return to her room.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.24,0:16:30.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As proof of this,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.46,0:16:34.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yumi rushed back to her room\Nstill holding the racket.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.61,0:16:36.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why her right hand which held the gun
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.61,0:16:40.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,had stiffened in the shakehand grip!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.03,0:16:43.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So the Yumi I saw right after 5:00 was—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.10,0:16:44.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Was the real Yumi, in the flesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.99,0:16:47.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She was still alive then.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.12,0:16:49.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She was watching the ping-pong\Nroom from the second floor
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.23,0:16:52.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and waiting for Nakamichi to be all alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.18,0:16:54.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yumi was probably really murdered
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.66,0:16:57.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,at 6:30, when the fireworks show started!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.42,0:17:01.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The gunshot would seem inconspicuous\Nwith all the fireworks exploding about!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.06,0:17:07.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But Nakamichi still had the job
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.82,0:17:10.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,of wiping off the body's sweat\Nand{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ging the clothes—
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.53,0:17:12.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,there was a{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ce the trick could be discovered
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.91,0:17:15.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,if we learned that she had been sweating.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.66,0:17:18.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He had no choice but to\Nremove her undergarments,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.37,0:17:20.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but he did{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ge her yukata...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.37,0:17:22.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...with a spare one.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.89,0:17:27.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But in the middle of his work,\Nan unforeseen obstacle appeared:
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.27,0:17:30.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran and Conan, who came to wake Yumi up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.62,0:17:33.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You stopped your work halfway through,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.99,0:17:37.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,exited onto the roof through the window,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.15,0:17:40.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and stopped Ran from entering the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.84,0:17:45.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You then went with everyone to see the fireworks,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.85,0:17:48.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,pretended to get separated,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.05,0:17:50.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and finished the rest of your work.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.46,0:17:56.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's when you put the gun in her hand\Nto make it look like a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.90,0:17:59.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Though it would seem that her hand
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.51,0:18:02.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,had already stiffened into that peculiar grip,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.34,0:18:05.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,making it impossible to put\Nher finger on the trigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.93,0:18:09.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your theory is indeed interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.57,0:18:13.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But do you have any proof that I did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.31,0:18:14.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be a fool!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.57,0:18:18.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The only person besides me who could've\Npulled that off was you, a police detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.77,0:18:22.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See! You could've done it as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.28,0:18:26.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And besides, anybody could\Nlearn that from a book.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.75,0:18:28.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Why, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.49,0:18:34.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You sure are dumb, old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.11,0:18:37.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This great policeman couldn't\Npossibly be the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.00,0:18:38.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Great policeman?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.44,0:18:39.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.76,0:18:44.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He knew that Yumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was dead\Njust by seeing her covered in blood!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.61,0:18:50.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You said the following\Nwithout ever touching Yumi...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.06,0:18:51.15,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Yumi!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.15,0:18:52.30,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Don't touch her!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.30,0:18:56.60,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Nobody but me and Mouri are to\Ncome in here, since we're detectives!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.60,0:18:59.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,For some reason you called not for an ambulance,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.65,0:19:01.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but for the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.90,0:19:05.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You knew that it was too late!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.71,0:19:07.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Because you killed her!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.69,0:19:10.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How could you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.39,0:19:11.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.90,0:19:13.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't want to kill her!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.53,0:19:16.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We went out for 18 years, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.42,0:19:17.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,E-Eighteen years?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.46,0:19:19.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.50,0:19:21.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Until I met someone half a year ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.85,0:19:25.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You did this because she\Nwould hinder your marriage?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.27,0:19:29.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why? Why didn't you marry her?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.16,0:19:30.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let go!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.36,0:19:34.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I proposed to her many times!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.55,0:19:37.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But her answer was always no!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.01,0:19:39.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,For 18 long years!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.65,0:19:43.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just when I was about to marry someone else,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.73,0:19:45.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yumi told me this:
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.00,0:19:48.73,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I won't allow it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.73,0:19:51.07,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I won't allow you to be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.07,0:19:57.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's when her threatening letters\Nand phone calls to my fiancée started.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.78,0:20:02.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Finally she said she was going to\Nsend photos of just the two of us!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.59,0:20:05.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I told her that if she brought\Nthe photos to the reunion
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.25,0:20:08.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I would buy them all off of her.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.47,0:20:12.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That was the day you caught the bank robber.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.35,0:20:15.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I had just met with Yumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.80,0:20:19.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was struggling over what to do about her...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.77,0:20:24.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...when the robber's gun fell nearby.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.45,0:20:27.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was then that I thought up this plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.29,0:20:31.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The deal was to take place\Nin the ping-pong room,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.99,0:20:33.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but then I told her this:
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.61,0:20:37.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The photos have been\Nremoved from your things.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.90,0:20:38.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.98,0:20:42.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why Yumi rushed back to her room,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.07,0:20:44.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,racket still in hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.42,0:20:47.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And you followed behind and shot her!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.31,0:20:48.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.49,0:20:51.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I shot the demon who screwed up my life!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.67,0:20:54.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Which one was the demon?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.03,0:20:54.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.94,0:20:57.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell would you know?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.00,0:21:00.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll never know...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.75,0:21:03.68,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}...how a murderer feels...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.68,0:21:05.66,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}...no matter what the reason!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.62,0:21:11.37,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I don't want to know!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.39,0:21:14.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.57,0:21:17.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Seems you're still as strong as ever...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.96,0:21:21.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be stupid. You've just gotten weaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.65,0:21:24.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Both your mind and your body.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.06,0:21:24.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.89,0:23:05.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's been pretty glum lately...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.76,0:23:09.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't blame him. Those were his friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.12,0:23:10.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That reminds me...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.87,0:23:14.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If he's that strong, why didn't he ever win any matches?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.03,0:23:19.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, in actual matches he gets so tense\Nthat he can't concentrate his strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.98,0:23:23.03,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}So he had a knack for being outdone...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.44,0:23:25.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go try to cheer him up...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.26,0:23:26.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.61,0:23:29.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's leave him alone for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.80,0:23:31.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He'll be back to normal eventually.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.21,0:23:43.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This time it's pink!
